  <dsc><c01 id="aspace_5503d857bc94112d0163547f93927ad1" level="item"><did><unittitle>Hector Falls Dry Goods Store Daybook,</unittitle><unitid>Item 1</unitid><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1822/1824" type="inclusive">(1822-1824)</unitdate></did><scopecontent id="aspace_b64aee1c4f178183327c9c30768f4f8c"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>54l pages containing name of customer, purchases, and whether paid by cash or draft.</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 id="aspace_3a2935896781c20a56871497aefd6468" level="item"><did><unittitle>Unidentified ledger</unittitle><unitid>Item 2</unitid><unitdate calendar="gregorian" certainty="approximate" era="ce" normal="1822-12-24/1824-08-13" type="inclusive">(Dec. 24, 1822-Aug. 13, 1824)</unitdate></did><scopecontent id="aspace_47e76d97008cdcb2193bee5938585182"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Contains an alphabetical index to names of individuals with accounts, and customer accounts for newspaper subscriptions or individual copies.</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 id="aspace_76cc6f4cf22014f0cd13ddfcea12fc69" level="item"><did><unittitle>Account Book</unittitle><unitid>Item 3</unitid><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce">(June 16, l825-0ct. 13, 1826)</unitdate></did><scopecontent id="aspace_281a7839e06bbc4380a062f9ae8fb097"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Microfilm copy. 54l pages. A 16" by 7" leather bound volume, marked "Journal," the pages are headed with "Hector Falls." Entries as in item 1.</p></scopecontent></c01><c01 id="aspace_f4901303197608f964d197305cca34b1" level="item"><did><unittitle>Ino H. Osborn &amp; Co., Account Book.</unittitle><unitid>Item 4</unitid><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1823-01-03/1826-05-09" type="inclusive">(Jan. 3, 1823-May 9, 1826)</unitdate></did><scopecontent id="aspace_d6d2d782ed474f865c2cfa672214e5dc"><head>Scope and Contents</head><p>Microfilm copy. pt. 1: List of customers who exchanged ashes for goods or cash, pt. 2: 7 pages of receipts for grapes, n.d., and list of customers of hoop poles (Jan. 1, 1823-Feb. 3, 1826)</p></scopecontent></c01></dsc>
